<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJoseph_Fourier.2C_translated_by_Alexander_Freemanpublished_1822.2C_translated_1878.2C_re-released_2003">Joseph Fourier, translated by Alexander Freeman (published 1822, translated 1878, re-released 2003). <i>The Analytical Theory of Heat</i>. Dover Publications. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486495310" class="internal">ISBN 0-486-49531-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Analytical+Theory+of+Heat&amp;rft.aulast=Joseph+Fourier%2C+translated+by+Alexander+Freeman&amp;rft.au=Joseph+Fourier%2C+translated+by+Alexander+Freeman&amp;rft.date=published+1822%2C+translated+1878%2C+re-released+2003&amp;rft.pub=Dover+Publications&amp;rft.isbn=0-486-49531-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fourier_series"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> 2003 unabridged republication of the 1878 English translation by Alexander Freeman of Fourier's work <i>Théorie Analytique de la Chaleur</i>, originally published in 1822.</li>
